key.doc.discussion.Para: You can construct URLs and access their parts. For URLs that represent local files, you can also manipulate properties of those files directly, such as changing the files last modification date. Finally, you can pass URLs to other APIs to retrieve the contents of those URLs. For example, you can use the URLSession classes to access the contents of remote resources, as described in URL Session Programming Guide.

URLs are the preferred way to refer to local files. Most objects that read data from or write data to a file have methods that accept a URL instead of a pathname as the file reference. For example, you can get the contents of a local file URL as `String` by calling `func init(contentsOf:encoding) throws`, or as a `Data` by calling `func init(contentsOf:options) throws`.
